sonetConfigTable.name: sonetConfigTable
sonetConfigTable.description: The SONET Configuration table. There is one row for each SONET port in the BASIS system. The table size (number of rows) is given by the value of sonetLineNumOfValidEntries.

sonetConfigEntry.name: sonetConfigEntry
sonetConfigEntry.description: An entry in the SONET Configuration table.

sonetLineNum.name: sonetLineNum
sonetLineNum.description: This object is the identifier of a SONET Interface on a managed device. For MGX8850(For example PXM1 Module): OC-3 : sonetLineNum in a range 1..4 OC-12: sonetLineNum = 1 is the ONLY valid number For Other: sonetLineNum = 1 is the ONLY valid number

sonetLineType.name: sonetLineType
sonetLineType.description: This variable indicates the cell framing. Defaults to Sts-3c

sonetLineLoopbackCommand.name: sonetLineLoopbackCommand
sonetLineLoopbackCommand.description: This variable represents the loopback configuration of the SONET interface. The values mean: sonetNoLoop Not in the loopback state. A device that is not capable of performing a loopback on the interface shall always return this as it's value. sonetRemoteLineLoop Near End loops back Remote data sonetLocalLineLoop Near End loops back Local data.

sonetPayloadScrambling.name: sonetPayloadScrambling
sonetPayloadScrambling.description: STS3c or STM-1 payload scrambling. Defaults to enable.

sonetFrameScrambling.name: sonetFrameScrambling
sonetFrameScrambling.description: STS3c or STM-1 frame scrambling. Defaults to enable.

sonetLineEnable.name: sonetLineEnable
sonetLineEnable.description: This variable indicates if the line is enabled or not defaults to disable

sonetLineXmtClkSrc.name: sonetLineXmtClkSrc
sonetLineXmtClkSrc.description: This represents the type of transmit clock source. backplaneClk: clock source is from the controller card, transmitted via the backplane to the service module. recoverClk: clock is recovered from the received signal. localClk: clock is from a local oscillator on the card. Default is backplaneClk.

sonetRDIVType.name: sonetRDIVType
sonetRDIVType.description: This variable represents the type of RDI-V sent by this NE to remote NE. onebit: use 1 bit RDI-V. Compatible with older equipment. threebit: use 3 bit, enhanced RDI-V. Defaults to onebit.

sonetRDIPType.name: sonetRDIPType
sonetRDIPType.description: This variable represents the type of RDI-P sent by this NE to remote NE. onebit: use 1 bit RDI-P. Compatible with older equipment. threebit: use 3 bit, enhanced RDI-P. Defaults to onebit.

sonetTributaryType.name: sonetTributaryType
sonetTributaryType.description: Type of tributary carried within the Sonet/Sdh signal. vt15vc11: carries T1 signals (VT15 or VC11) vt2vc12: carries E1 signals (VT2 or VC12) Default is vt15vc11 for Sonet interfaces and vt2vc12 for SDH interfaces.

sonetTributaryMappingType.name: sonetTributaryMappingType
sonetTributaryMappingType.description: Type of VT/VC mapping. asynchronous: In this mode, the channel structure of the DS1/E1 is neither visible nor preserved. byteSynchronous: In this mode, the DS0 channels inside the VC/VT can be found and extracted. Default is asynchronous.

sonetTributaryFramingFormat.name: sonetTributaryFramingFormat
sonetTributaryFramingFormat.description: Type of vt framing format. Is applicable only in byte-sync mapping mode for T1 tributaries. notApplicable: if VT mapping is not byte-sync. sf: superframe format. esf: extended superframe format. Default is esf if sonetTributaryMappingType is set to byteSynchronous, else the default is notApplicable.

sonetSignallingTransportMode.name: sonetSignallingTransportMode
sonetSignallingTransportMode.description: The mode used to transport DS0 signalling information for T1 byte-sync mapping. notApplicable: if byte-sync mapping is not used. signallingTransferMode: the robbed bit signalling is transferred into the S bits of the VT header and framing bit is discarded. clearMode: only the framing bit is transferred to VT header. The signalling bits are left intact in the VT payload. Default is signallingTransferMode if sonetTributaryMappingType is set to byteSynchronous, else the default is notApplicable.

sonetTributaryGroupingType.name: sonetTributaryGroupingType
sonetTributaryGroupingType.description: This variable indicates the method used to group VCs into an STM-1 signal. Applicable only to SDH. notApplicable: for sonet interfaces. au3Grouping: STM-1 <- AU-3 <- TUG-2 <- TU-12 <- VC12 or STM-1 <- AU-3 <- TUG-2 <- TU-11 <- VC11. au4Grouping: STM-1 <- AU-4 <- TUG-3 <- TUG-2 <- TU-12 <- VC12 or STM-1 <- AU-4 <- TUG-3 <- TUG-2 <- TU-11 <- VC11. Defaults to au3Grouping for SDH interfaces and notApplicable for Sonet interfaces.

sonetConfigNumOfValidEntries.name: sonetConfigNumOfValidEntries
sonetConfigNumOfValidEntries.description: The number of SONET configuration entries (regardless of their current configuration) in the sonetConfigTable.

cwSonetMediumEntry.name: cwSonetMediumEntry
cwSonetMediumEntry.description: An entry in the SONET/SDH Medium table.

cwSonetMediumType.name: cwSonetMediumType
cwSonetMediumType.description: This variable identifies whether a SONET or a SDH signal is used across this interface.

cwSonetMediumTimeElapsed.name: cwSonetMediumTimeElapsed
cwSonetMediumTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds, including partial seconds, that have elapsed since the beginning of the mandatory error-measurement period.

cwSonetMediumValidIntervals.name: cwSonetMediumValidIntervals
cwSonetMediumValidIntervals.description: The number of previous intervals for which valid data has been stored. A SONET device must support at least n intervals. The minimum value of n is 4. The default of n is 32. The maximum value of n is 96. The value of this object will be n unless the device was brought online within the last (nx15) minutes, in which case the value will be the number of complete 15 minute intervals the device has been online.

cwSonetMediumLineCoding.name: cwSonetMediumLineCoding
cwSonetMediumLineCoding.description: This variable describes the line coding for this interface. The B3ZS and CMI are used for electrical SONET/SDH signals (STS-1 and STS-3). The Non-Return to Zero (NRZ) and the Return to Zero are used for optical SONET/SDH signals.

cwSonetMediumLineType.name: cwSonetMediumLineType
cwSonetMediumLineType.description: This variable describes the line type for this interface. The line types are Short and Long Range Single Mode fiber or Multi-Mode fiber interfaces, and coax and UTP for electrical interfaces. The value sonetOther should be used when the Line Type is not one of the listed values.

cwSonetMediumCircuitIdentifier.name: cwSonetMediumCircuitIdentifier
cwSonetMediumCircuitIdentifier.description: This variable contains the transmission vendor's circuit identifier, for the purpose of facilitating troubleshooting.

cwSonetSectionCurrentEntry.name: cwSonetSectionCurrentEntry
cwSonetSectionCurrentEntry.description: An entry in the SONET/SDH Section Current table.

cwSonetSectionCurrentLineNum.name: cwSonetSectionCurrentLineNum
cwSonetSectionCurrentLineNum.description: line number. There are Max 1 line Num

cwSonetSectionCurrentStatus.name: cwSonetSectionCurrentStatus
cwSonetSectionCurrentStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of the sonet section layer. The cwSonetSectionCurrentStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple defects simultaneously. The sonetSectionNoDefect should be set if and only if no other flag is set. The various bit positions are: bit 1 = sonetSectionNoDefect bit 2 = sonetSectionLOS bit 3 = sonetSectionLOF

cwSonetSectionCurrentValidFlag.name: cwSonetSectionCurrentValidFlag
cwSonetSectionCurrentValidFlag.description: Indicates if the current 15min bucket is valid or not.

cwSonetSectionCurrent15minTimeElapsed.name: cwSonetSectionCurrent15minTimeElapsed
cwSonetSectionCurrent15minTimeElapsed.description: The number of seconds, including partial seconds, that have elapsed since the beginning of the 15min error-measurement period.

cwSonetSectionCurrentESs.name: cwSonetSectionCurrentESs
cwSonetSectionCurrentESs.description: The counter associated with the number of Errored Seconds encountered by a SONET/SDH Section in the current 15 minute interval.

cwSonetSectionCurrentSESs.name: cwSonetSectionCurrentSESs
cwSonetSectionCurrentSESs.description: The counter associated with the number of Severely Errored Seconds encountered by a SONET/SDH Section in the current 15 minute interval.

cwSonetSectionCurrentSEFSs.name: cwSonetSectionCurrentSEFSs

cwSonetSectionCurrentCVs.name: cwSonetSectionCurrentCVs

cwSonetSectionCurrentClrButton.name: cwSonetSectionCurrentClrButton
cwSonetSectionCurrentClrButton.description: Clears all the Section's Current15min counters.

cwSonetSectionIntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, which identifies the interval for which the set of statistics is available. The interval identified by 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval, and the interval identified by N is the interval immediately preceding the one identified by N-1.

cwSonetSectionIntervalValidFlag.name: cwSonetSectionIntervalValidFlag

sonetSectionTraceToTransmit.name: sonetSectionTraceToTransmit
sonetSectionTraceToTransmit.description: Sonet Section Trace To Transmit. 16-64 bytes String. If 16 byte trace is selected, FW will only use bytes 0-15 of the string.

sonetSectionTraceToExpect.name: sonetSectionTraceToExpect
sonetSectionTraceToExpect.description: Sonet Section Trace To Expect. 16-64 bytes String. If 16 byte trace is selected, FW will only use bytes 0-15 of the string.

sonetSectionTraceReceived.name: sonetSectionTraceReceived
sonetSectionTraceReceived.description: Sonet Section Trace Received. 16-64 bytes String. The write option is for debugging only.

sonetSectionStatAlarmStatus.name: sonetSectionStatAlarmStatus
sonetSectionStatAlarmStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of the interface. The sonetSectionStatAlarmStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple defects simultaneously. The sonetLineStatAlarmNoDefect should be set if and only if no other flag is set. The various bit positions are: 1 sonetSectionStatAlarmNoDefect 2 sonetSectionCurrent15minESs 3 sonetSectionCurrent15minSESs 4 sonetSectionCurrent15minSEFSs 5 sonetSectionCurrent15minCVs 6 sonetSectionCurrentDayESs 7 sonetSectionCurrentDaySESs 8 sonetSectionCurrentDaySEFSs 9 sonetSectionCurrentDayCVs

sonetSectionCounterEntry.name: sonetSectionCounterEntry
sonetSectionCounterEntry.description: An entry in the SONET/SDH Section table.
